      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "FEA software (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) is under formal configuration management with version-controlled input decks. Software validation reports for linear static solvers are on file. Achieved level 3 reflects documented regression testing and independent code verification activities performed by DePuy Synthes and FDA teams."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed via comparison with analytical beam-bending solutions for simplified cantilever geometries matching the pedicle screw aspect ratio. Residual norms monitored to convergence tolerance of 1e-8. Three independent analysts reproduced reference solutions within 0.3%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study conducted with three systematically refined meshes (coarse: 42k elements, medium: 168k elements, fine: 672k elements). Richardson extrapolation applied; discretization error in peak von Mises stress estimated at 1.8%. Final mesh selected at medium refinement level with GCI < 3%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Direct sparse solver (SPARSE) employed for linear static analysis. Iterative solver residuals confirmed below 1e-10. Condition number of stiffness matrix evaluated and confirmed well-conditioned (kappa < 1e6) for all 11 construct configurations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow documented in a controlled simulation plan. Independent analyst review of boundary condition assignments and material property inputs performed prior to each analysis run. Checklist-based QC gate enforced before result extraction."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum FEA with frictional contact interfaces selected based on prior literature for metallic spinal implant constructs under quasi-static loading. Model form assumptions (small deformation, isotropic Ti-6Al-4V material) justified by strain gauge measurements confirming sub-yield deformation regime throughout F1717 test protocol."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from ASTM F136 certificates of conformance for the specific Ti-6Al-4V bar stock used in device manufacture. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of N=3 representative screw samples. Boundary condition inputs (applied displacement, fixture stiffness) calibrated against load-cell data from the experimental test frame."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Samples drawn from the same production lot with documented traceability. Sample size exceeds ASME V&V 40 minimum recommendation for medium model risk; inter-laboratory variability assessed via ANOVA."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single load level (1500 N axial compression with 10 Nm bending moment) per ASTM F1717 protocol. Required level 3 demands multi-condition coverage; only one test condition evaluated in this study, resulting in achieved level 2. This shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given the standardized nature of the F1717 protocol and the regulatory precedent for single-condition submission."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Simulation input parameters mapped directly to experimentally measured quantities. Fixture geometry, applied loads, and material properties used in simulation are traceable to the same physical measurements used in the experimental protocol. Parameter equivalency matrix documented and reviewed by all three participating organizations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using mean absolute percentage error (MAPE) and Theil's inequality coefficient. FEA predictions of construct stiffness and peak bending moment at yield agree with experimental means within 8.2% across all 11 constructs. Bland-Altman analysis confirms no systematic bias. Prediction intervals overlap experimental 95% confidence intervals for all constructs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Quantities of interest (construct stiffness, peak bending moment at structural yield) are directly relevant to the clinical failure modes of pedicle screw constructs under physiological compression-bending loading. QoI selection validated against FDA guidance on spinal implant mechanical performance and confirmed with clinical biomechanics literature."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk category.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities performed using the identical device geometry, material, and loading protocol as the intended regulatory submission context. ASTM F1717 is the recognized consensus standard for this device type. The validation domain fully encompasses the intended simulation use scope as described in the Claim and Requirement nodes, supporting the credibility argument for regulatory decision-making."
    }
