    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved 2, required 3) is accepted given the standardized single-condition nature of ASTM F1717 and established regulatory precedent. Overall model credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending FEA model. Decision: Accepted.",
